comments: Hart (NOP) moves through WIlliams III's (BOS) space and dislodges him from his screening position.
Fournier (BOS) is already in Hart's (NOP) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Ingram (NOP) and Tatum (BOS) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Bledsoe (NOP) does not maintain verticality and he makes contact with Walker's (BOS) arm as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Adams (NOP) and Smart (BOS) briefly engage and disengage as they position themselves for a potential rebound.
Smart (BOS) is moving alongside Williamson's (NOP) path and maintains a legal guarding position on the perimeter.
Adams (NOP) is already in Smart's (BOS) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Smart (BOS) moves somewhat forward towards Williamson (NOP), and the contact on the perimeter is marginal.
Williams III (BOS) is moving alongside Williamson's (NOP) path and maintains a legal guarding position as he defends the drive.
Tatum (BOS) makes clean contact with the ball as he defends Williamson's (NOP) driving shot attempt.
After initially making contact with the ball, WIlliamson (NOP) makes some marginal contact with Williams III's (BOS) arm, and Williams III quickly regains possession of the ball.
Adams (NOP) legally contests Tatum's (BOS) jump shot attempt.
Walker (BOS) brushes Alexander-Walker's (NOP) arm as he is passing the ball, and contact is marginal.

As Tatum's (BOS) momentum carries him towards the basket, his hand makes some contact with Ingram's (NOP) head.   Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Ingram (NOP) is bracing for the contact from Tatum (BOS) and releases away from the contact.

Smart (BOS) sets the screen on Adams (NOP) without giving him room to avoid the contact.  He then places his arm around his waist and pulls him as he goes to the ground, affecting his FOM.  Adams does not move through Smart's space and dislodge him from his position.
Hart (NOP) absorbs the marginal contact initiated by Tatum (BOS) and legally contests his shot attempt.
All Technical Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Williams (BOS) makes contact with Williamson (NOP) after he has secured the rebound that affects his SQBR.
Ingram (NOP) legally contests Walker's (BOS) driving shot attempt.
Tatum (BOS) commits a take foul on Williamson (NOP).
Adams (NOP) is moving alongside Tatum's (BOS) path and maintains a legal guarding position on the perimeter.
